# Create a sequence of years from 1980 to 2023
all_years <- data.frame(Year = 1980:2023)

#Winsorization, (Duplicates were removed at the excel level)
# Define the numeric columns to be winsorized
numeric_columns <- c('total_assets', 'dividends', 'loss_adj_expenses', 'loss_incurred', 
                     'net_income', 'net_investment_income', 'other_uw_expenses', 
                     'phs', 'total_liab', 'total_prem_earned')

# Define the lower and upper percentiles
lower_percentile <- 0.005  # 0.5th percentile
upper_percentile <- 0.995  # 99.5th percentile

# Group by year and apply winsorization to numeric columns
FirmYearData_winsorized <- FirmYearData %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  mutate(across(all_of(numeric_columns), ~ {
    lower_bound <- quantile(., lower_percentile)
    upper_bound <- quantile(., upper_percentile)
    replace(., . < lower_bound, lower_bound)
    replace(., . > upper_bound, upper_bound)
  }))

# Print the winsorized data
print(FirmYearData_winsorized)

library(dplyr)

# Calculate leverage ratio per year (sum of 'phs' for all firms)
leverage_ratio <- FirmYearData_winsorized %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarize(leverage_ratio = sum(phs))

# Calculate premiums to P/H surplus
premiums_to_phs <- FirmYearData_winsorized %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarize(premiums_to_phs = sum(total_prem_earned) / sum(phs))

# Calculate liabilities to P/H surplus
liabilities_to_phs <- FirmYearData_winsorized %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarize(liabilities_to_phs = sum(total_liab) / sum(phs))

# Combine results into a single table

#Q6 PANEL b

# Filter data for the specified organizational forms and exclude Lloyds and Risk Retention Groups
filtered_data <- FirmYearData_winsorized %>%
  filter(!org_form %in% c("Lloyd's", "RRG")) %>%
  mutate(
    org_form_combined = ifelse(org_form %in% c("Mutual", "Reciprocal"), "Mutual/Reciprocal", as.character(org_form))
  )

# Calculate aggregated values for each organizational form by year
aggregated_data <- filtered_data %>%
  group_by(year, org_form_combined) %>%
  summarise(
    total_other_uw_expenses = sum(other_uw_expenses),
    total_loss_incurred = sum(loss_incurred),
    total_loss_adj_expenses = sum(loss_adj_expenses),
    total_net_investment_income = sum(net_investment_income),
    total_total_prem_earned = sum(total_prem_earned)
  )
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
# Calculate operating ratio for each organizational form
aggregated_data <- aggregated_data %>%
  mutate(
    operating_ratio = (total_other_uw_expenses + total_loss_incurred + total_loss_adj_expenses) /
      total_total_prem_earned -
      (total_net_investment_income / total_total_prem_earned)
  )

# Create a sequence of years from 1996 to 2019
years_sequence <- seq(1996, 2019, by = 1)

# Plot the operating ratio for each organizational form over years

  geom_line() +
  labs(
    title = "Operating Ratio by Organizational Form",
    x = "Year",
    y = "Operating Ratio",

# Define the numeric columns to be winsorized
numeric_columns <- c('dpw', 'reinsurance_assumed', 'npw')

# Define the lower and upper percentiles
lower_percentile <- 0.005  # 0.5th percentile
upper_percentile <- 0.995  # 99.5th percentile

# Group by year and lob, and apply winsorization to numeric columns
FirmLineYearData_winsorized <- FirmLineYearData %>%
  group_by(year, lob) %>%
  mutate(across(all_of(numeric_columns), ~ {
    lower_bound <- quantile(., lower_percentile)
    upper_bound <- quantile(., upper_percentile)
    replace(., . < lower_bound, lower_bound)
    replace(., . > upper_bound, upper_bound)
  }))
print(FirmLineYearData_winsorized)

#Q9 

# Load required libraries
library(dplyr)

# Define the lines of insurance and their corresponding columns
lines_of_insurance <- list(
  "Personal Auto" = c("Personal Auto - Liability", "Personal Auto - PD"),
  "Commercial Auto" = c("Commercial Auto - Liability", "Commercial Auto - PD"),
  "Homeowners + Farmowners" = c("Homeowners", "Farmowners"),
  "Fire + Allied Lines" = c("Fire", "Allied"),
  "Commercial Multiple Peril" = c("Commercial Multiple Peril"),
  "General Liability" = c("General Liability"),
  "Medical Prof. Liability" = c("Medical Prof. Liability"),
  "Workers' Compensation" = c("Workers' Compensation"),
  "Inland Marine + Ocean Marine" = c("Inland Marine", "Ocean Marine"),
  "Other" = c("Air", "Boiler and Machinery", "Burglary and Theft", "Earth Movement", "Financial", "Warranty")
)

# Aggregate the "lob" values based on the defined lines of insurance
aggregate_lob <- function(lob) {
  for (category in names(lines_of_insurance)) {
    if (lob %in% lines_of_insurance[[category]]) {
      return(category)
    }
  }
  return("Other")
}

# Apply the aggregation function to the "lob" column
FirmLineYearData_winsorized$lob <- sapply(FirmLineYearData_winsorized$lob, aggregate_lob)

# Initialize a data frame to store the results
result <- data.frame(lob = character(), year = integer(), npw_percentage = double())

# Loop over years and calculate NPW percentage for each line of insurance
for (year in c(2001, 2005, 2009, 2013, 2018)) {
  # Filter data for the current year
  data_year <- FirmLineYearData_winsorized[FirmLineYearData_winsorized$year == year, ]
  
  # Calculate total NPW for the current year
  total_npw_year <- sum(data_year$npw)
  
  # Loop over lines of insurance and calculate NPW percentage
  for (lob_name in names(lines_of_insurance)) {
    npw_lob_year <- sum(data_year[data_year$lob == lob_name, "npw"])
    npw_percentage <- (npw_lob_year / total_npw_year) * 100
    
    # Add the result to the data frame
    result <- rbind(result, data.frame(lob = lob_name, year = year, npw_percentage = npw_percentage))
  }
}

# Pivot the data to create a table
npw_table <- pivot_wider(result, names_from = year, values_from = npw_percentage, values_fill = 0)

# Print the result
print("Net Premiums Written in Property-Liability Insurance (percent of total premiums written), by Line of Insurance:")
## [1] "Net Premiums Written in Property-Liability Insurance (percent of total premiums written), by Line of Insurance:"
print(npw_table)

# Plotting function for side-by-side bar chart

  ggplot(data, aes(x = year, y = Market_Share_Normalized, fill = org_form)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
    labs(title = title,
         x = "Years",
         y = "Normalized Market Share",
         fill = "Organizational Form") +

    theme_minimal() +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust = 1)) +  # Rotate x-axis labels vertically
    theme(legend.position = "bottom")  # Adjust legend position
}

filtered_data <- merged_data %>%
  mutate(Distribution_System = ifelse(distribution_system %in% direct_systems, "Direct", "Independent"))

# Calculate total net premiums written for each year
total_premiums_by_year <- filtered_data %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarise(total_npw = sum(npw))

# Calculate market share for each distribution system
market_share_data <- filtered_data %>%
  group_by(year, Distribution_System, insurance_type) %>%
  summarise(dist_system_npw = sum(npw)) %>%
  left_join(total_premiums_by_year, by = "year") %>%
  mutate(Market_Share = dist_system_npw / total_npw)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year', 'Distribution_System'. You can
## override using the `.groups` argument.
# Normalize market share within each line of insurance (Personal and Commercial)
normalized_market_share_data <- market_share_data %>%
  group_by(year, insurance_type) %>%
  mutate(Market_Share_Normalized = Market_Share / sum(Market_Share)) %>%
  ungroup()  # Remove grouping

# Plotting function for non-stacked bar graph
plot_market_share_bar <- function(data, title) {
  ggplot(data, aes(x = year, y = Market_Share_Normalized, fill = Distribution_System)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
    labs(title = title,
         x = "Years",
         y = "Normalized Market Share",
         fill = "Distribution System") +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(1996, 2019, by = 1)) +  # Set breaks for all years
    theme_minimal() +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust = 1)) +  # Rotate x-axis labels vertically
    theme(legend.position = "bottom")  # Adjust legend position
}

# Create non-stacked bar plots for each panel
bar_panel_b <- plot_market_share_bar(filter(normalized_market_share_data, insurance_type == "Personal"), "Market Share by Distribution System (Personal Lines)")
bar_panel_c <- plot_market_share_bar(filter(normalized_market_share_data, insurance_type == "Commercial"), "Market Share by Distribution System (Commercial Lines)")

# Display non-stacked bar plots
print(bar_panel_b)

print(bar_panel_c)

# Load data

  filter(year == 2001)

  filter(year == 2019)

filtered_firm_line_year_data_2019 <- firm_line_year_data %>%
  filter(year == 2019)

# Merge the filtered dataframes on common columns
merged_data_2001 <- merge(filtered_firm_year_data_2001, filtered_firm_line_year_data_2001, by=c('cocode', 'year'))
merged_data_2019 <- merge(filtered_firm_year_data_2019, filtered_firm_line_year_data_2019, by=c('cocode', 'year'))

# Combine "Mutual" and "Reciprocal" into one category called "Mutual"
merged_data_2001$org_form <- ifelse(merged_data_2001$org_form %in% c("Mutual", "Reciprocal"), "Mutual+Reciprocal", merged_data_2001$org_form)
merged_data_2019$org_form <- ifelse(merged_data_2019$org_form %in% c("Mutual", "Reciprocal"), "Mutual+Reciprocal", merged_data_2019$org_form)

# Function to calculate market share
calculate_market_share <- function(data) {
  total_premiums_by_year <- data %>%
    filter(org_form %in% c("Mutual+Reciprocal", "Stock")) %>%
    group_by(org_form) %>%
    summarise(total_npw = sum(npw))
  
  market_share_data <- data %>%
    filter(org_form %in% c("Mutual+Reciprocal", "Stock")) %>%
    group_by(org_form, lob) %>%
    summarise(org_form_npw = sum(npw)) %>%
    left_join(total_premiums_by_year, by="org_form") %>%
    mutate(Market_Share = org_form_npw / total_npw)
  
  return(market_share_data)
}

# Calculate market share for each org_form for 2001 and 2019
market_share_data_2001 <- calculate_market_share(merged_data_2001)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'org_form'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
market_share_data_2019 <- calculate_market_share(merged_data_2019)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'org_form'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
# Create plots for 2001 and 2019
plot_2001 <- ggplot(market_share_data_2001, aes(x = lob, y = Market_Share, fill = org_form)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
  labs(title = "Market Share by Line of Business (2001)",
       x = "Line of Business",
       y = "Market Share") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

plot_2019 <- ggplot(market_share_data_2019, aes(x = lob, y = Market_Share, fill = org_form)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
  labs(title = "Market Share by Line of Business (2019)",
       x = "Line of Business",
       y = "Market Share") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

# Print the plots
print(plot_2001)

  filter(year == 2001)

  filter(year == 2019)

  filter(year == 2019)

# Merge the filtered dataframes on common columns
merged_data_2001 <- merge(filtered_firm_year_data_2001, filtered_firm_line_year_data_2001, by = c('cocode', 'year'))
merged_data_2019 <- merge(filtered_firm_year_data_2019, filtered_firm_line_year_data_2019, by = c('cocode', 'year'))

# Combine "Direct" and "Captive" into one category called "Direct"

# Function to calculate market share
calculate_market_share <- function(data) {
  total_premiums_by_year <- data %>%
    group_by(year) %>%
    summarise(total_npw = sum(npw))
  
  market_share_data <- data %>%
    group_by(year, distribution_system, lob) %>%
    summarise(system_lob_npw = sum(npw)) %>%
    left_join(total_premiums_by_year, by = "year") %>%
    mutate(Market_Share = system_lob_npw / total_npw)
  
  return(market_share_data)
}
